The paper discusses standardization activities for machine-to-machine (M2M) communications in industry sectors such as Smart Grid and e-Health. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category, which deals with communication protocols, network architectures, and network algorithms. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category, as it discusses the security implications of M2M communications. The Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category is also a possibility, as the paper may discuss software development practices for M2M systems. The Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category may also be relevant, as the paper may discuss cryptographic protocols for securing M2M communications. Finally, the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category may be relevant, as the paper may discuss control systems for managing M2M networks.
